               <floruit notBefore="1799" notAfter="1801">
                  He was one of the puppet rulers of the Zamana masāfǝnt. When 
                  <persName ref="PRS8423Salomon">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Salomon III</persName> was 
                  deposed,  
                  <persName ref="PRS4871GugsaMe">
                     <roleName type="title">daǧǧāzmāč</roleName> 
                     Gugsā Mǝrč̣ā</persName>  and 
                  <persName ref="PRS1774Alula">
                     <roleName type="title">daǧǧāzmāč</roleName>  ʾAlulā</persName> made <persName ref="PRS3501Demetros">Dǝmeṭros</persName> an emperor at 
                  <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName> in 
                     <date>1799</date>. 
                  Then, he immediately rewarded his benefactors by appointing them to important positions. He was deposed in March <date>1800</date>
                  and succeeded by  
                  <persName ref="PRS9142TaklaGi">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> 
                     Takla Giyorgis I</persName>.  
                  <persName ref="PRS3501Demetros">Dǝmeṭros</persName> was restored in June <date>1800</date> and again deposed in <date>1801</date>.
               </floruit>
          
            </person>
